<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870127-0016 </DOCNO><HL> Coffee Exchange Reports3 Daily Trading Records</HL><DD> 01/27/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> COMMODITY NEWS, FARM PRODUCTS (CMD)SECURITIES INDUSTRY (SCR) </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Coffee, Sugar andamp; Cocoa Exchange said three trading-volume records were set Friday.    The exchange reported total volume of 57,732 contracts across the six it trades, topping the previous high of 45,976, set exactly a year earlier. The six contracts are coffee, sugar and cocoa futures plus options on each.    Sugar futures trading hit a high of 42,148 contracts, surpassing the record of 36,152 set April 18, 1982. Trading in options on the sugar futures also set a record with 3,287 calls and 966 puts, shattering the prior mark of 2,904 calls and 579 puts, set the day before, the exchange said. </TEXT></DOC>